ntext. Data from excavated wooden tablets, or slips (mokkan), is included as well as a chart of all the graphs and where they appear in the cited material. Students and scholars of Old Japanese writing and language and those more widely interested in the culture and history of pre-Heian Japan now have important linguistic and textual data at their fingertips arranged by character to help them decipher material from the ancient past.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 7aFOREIGN LANGUAGE STUDY / Japanese.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Hawaii Press Complete eBook-Package 2016z978311066323540uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978082485613740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780824856137423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780824856137/original  a978-3-11-066323-5  University of Hawaii Press Complete eBook-Package 2016b2016  aGBV-deGruyter-alles